  "text": "Research using data from betting on NBA games has examined bettor biases in the context of the efficient market hypothesis. [CITATION_1] examined the influence of the \"hot hand\" on point spreads for NBA games. The \"hot hand\" is a phenomenon where bettors misunderstand the randomness of events such as winning and losing streaks by sports teams.",
